# Expo Router Navigation

This project uses Expo Router for navigation. Always use the `useRouter` hook for programmatic navigation.

## Import and Usage

```tsx
import { useRouter } from "expo-router";

export default function MyComponent() {
  const router = useRouter();

  // Navigation methods
  router.push("/route"); // Navigate to route
  router.replace("/route"); // Replace current route
  router.back(); // Go back
}
```

## Route Structure

- **`/(auth)/login`** - Login page
- **`/(auth)/register`** - Registration page
- **`/(main)/home`** - Home page
- **`/(main)/profile`** - Profile page

## Navigation Patterns

- Use `router.replace()` for authentication flows (login → main app)
- Use `router.push()` for navigation within the same group
- Use `router.back()` to return to previous screen
- Always navigate to the full path including group prefix

## Important Notes

- Never import `router` directly - always use `useRouter()` hook
- The hook must be called inside a React component
- Route groups `(auth)` and `(main)` are used for layout organization
